bug.short_desc: kernel 4.10.8-100 starts agin, but recognize only one screen
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: The problem occurs since the arrival of kernel 4.9 on F24. The 4.8 series does not have a problem. See also bug 1415398. It need not to be a graphic card driver issue, it is a real freeze, that happens, when the start-scrren switches to the graphics mode, showing the blue-f Symbol.
No log is beeing saved until then ;-(
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): kernel 4.9.5-100 kernel 4.9.9-100
How reproducible: start your computer with 4.9 and got frozen!
Steps to Reproduce: 1. start your computer with 4.9 and got frozen! 2. 3.
Actual results: Start 4.8
Expected results: Kernel is running.
Additional info: System never had that problem before. Kernel 4.8 is running without any issues. + Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-3770K CPU @ 3.50GHz + 16GB ram + GPR4400 graphic card with 2 attached WQHD Displays via Displaylink

Let me know, iff you need further images.
Christian

Thanks for the picture. At this point, I think it makes sense to track this as a graphics issue. The fastest way to find the specific issue between 4.8 and 4.9 would be kernel bisection if you want to make the effort to do that.

(In reply to Laura Abbott from comment #5) > Thanks for the picture. At this point, I think it makes sense to track this > as a graphics issue. The fastest way to find the specific issue between 4.8 > and 4.9 would be kernel bisection if you want to make the effort to do that.
Good idea, i'll gonna route that issue to its new direction.
Thank you for your support Christian

Some (half) good news,
with kernel-4.10.8-100.fc24.x86_64 the kernel is not freezing anymore. While the system starts, i recognized a radeon error but the system starts running to the login screen with the expected resolution. The only thing that fails is the double-screen recognition of my two screen, so the system only duplicates the desktop on both screens.
Leave me a note, if you need any logs.

Apologies but I installed kernel-4.10.8-100.fc24.x86_64 today morning and have been facing the issue of the system freezing up since then :(
In my case, the freezing happens after I have logged in and have Firefox (50.0.2) / System Explorer for a few minutes or so. Another situation is when I leave the system unattended, causing the power-saving mode to kick in but after that when I try to log in, the system does not move forward at all, showing only a blank screen instead of the screen for accepting password.
By the way, I am writing this message by running the system with 4.9.17-100.fc24 kernel which seems just fine.
